<span id="freeTextContainer1083003358578039134">Most people appear to believe that the definitive novel about invisibility is H.G. Wells&apos;s <i>The Invisible Man</i>. This book is comparatively unknown, but IMHO far more interesting. I really liked it. <br/><br/>To start off with: what does &quot;invisible&quot; mean? It&apos;s not as obvious as one first thinks.<br/><br/></span>
  <span id="freeText1083003358578039134" style="display:none">Most people appear to believe that the definitive novel about invisibility is H.G. Wells's <i>The Invisible Man</i>. This book is comparatively unknown, but IMHO far more interesting. I really liked it. <br /><br />To start off with: what does "invisible" mean? It's not as obvious as one first thinks.<br /><br /></span>
