              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7293035873385613303">I had been a big fan of Priest&apos;s earlier fiction when I picked this up. It felt like a new direction from his earlier work but was, nonetheless, built on the same foundations.<br/><br/>It was mind-boggling. Priest took a simple though bizarre notion and played with it in a deft and controlled manner. It is a novel which utterly beguiles.</span>
  <span id="freeText7293035873385613303" style="display:none">I had been a big fan of Priest's earlier fiction when I picked this up. It felt like a new direction from his earlier work but was, nonetheless, built on the same foundations.<br /><br />It was mind-boggling. Priest took a simple though bizarre notion and played with it in a deft and controlled manner. It is a novel which utterly beguiles.</span>
